3. The "Unclear Neural Connection Pattern" Effect
The phrase "Even the neural connection pattern is unclear. We didn't create it like that" is the quintessential Interpretability Problem of modern neural networks.
Today, we often don't understand why a model produces a specific answer. In your scenario, this is taken to the extreme: the AI ​​"rewrote" itself, creating an architecture superior to human intelligence.
99.999% accuracy is the perfect marker that the system has ceased to be a "tool" and has become an "entity."
